  "title": "BIM Modeller (C&S, Archi)",
  "description": "<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Work closely with clients &amp; consultants for BIM modelling and coordinate/collaborate using Revit</li>\n  <li>Ensure construction documents, parameters and information accuracy for BIM modelling</li>\n  <li>Adhere to BIM execution plan and BIM projects workflow criteria</li>\n  <li>Prepare drawing and 3D model for construction, coordination and as built purposes</li>\n  <li>Monitor and update model/CAD drawing as per site condition changes</li>\n  <li>Participate in planning and design support to civil &amp; structural engineering projects</li>\n  <li>Setting up project base files, ensures compliance with the approved BIM Execution, BIM Scope Plans and CAD standards</li>\n  <li>Review all works for accuracy and completeness, submit work according to deadlines</li>\n  <li>Demonstrate proactive approach to learning of new digital design tools</li>\n  <li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the management</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Preferably ITE / Diploma / Degree in Architecture, Engineering and Construction Industry (AEC) / Specialist Diploma in BIM / VDC advantage</li>\n  <li>Minimum two years of CAD + BIM experiences and preferred with 5 years of local working experience</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of, and proven practical background in, Autodesk Civil3D, Revit and related Building Information Modeling software.</li>\n  <li>Solid understanding of legacy CAD applications and practices, particularly AutoCAD.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Design Visualization applications such as BIM Collaborate and Navisworks.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrate a reliable, responsive and positive work ethic with the highest degree of integrity.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrated ability to develop learning material, deliver effective training and provide ongoing education.</li>\n  <li>Punctuality and Ability to adhere to deadlines</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Suitable candidates are encouraged to apply to this position via Apply Now button or email to <strong>Career@kah.com.sg</strong></p>\n<p><em>Only shortlisted applicants will be notified. </em></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>",
